{
  "stem": "19210.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they could not-- the conditions was they could stay there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They arranged for-- for homes for them to stay, but they could not leave without a permit from the Portuguese government, the-- the immigration police.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I remember that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So ultimately-- ultimately, many-- many Jews were allowed to stay in Portugal and many of them stayed.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Was there a time when they started to think about immigration from Lisbon to Palestine?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because of the fact that there was-- at times, there were quite a few Jewish immigrants in Portugal, in Lisbon, interesting enough, there were times where there were large numbers of children that had been rescued from France and brought through Spain into Portugal.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a family in Lisbon by the name of Sequerra, S-E-Q-U-E-R-R-A, and Yoel Sequerra was employed, I believe, by the American Joint Committee.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he used to-- to work the corridor of France, Spain, Portugal, and sneak in Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and again, I believe also that he worked to a certain extent with Dr. de Sousa Mendes in getting visas from Dr. de Sousa Mendes for the children to cross through Spain into Portugal.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So when-- when we left Lisbon aboard the ship N-Y-S-S-A, on January 23rd, 1944, there were probably 300 or 400 children, refugees.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there were more-- the number of was larger than the adults, as a matter of fact.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And our first stop was in Cadiz, Spain, Port of Cadiz, C-A-D-I-Z.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And aboard came Yoel Sequerra with 360 children that had stayed in Cadiz and they also immigrated to Israel, their parents, to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So these things are-- are memories that will never leave you because you can see that there was many times happiness amongst these children.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
